quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
40,50,"The keepers of Hell will ask: “Did your Messengers not come to you with Clear Signs?” They will say: “Yes (they did).” The keepers of Hell will say: “Then you yourselves should call (upon the Lord). And the call of the unbelievers will end in vain.” {1}",footnotes:1:That is
40,51,"Surely We shall help Our Messengers and the believers in the life of this world {1} and on the Day when witnesses will rise to testify, {2}",footnotes:1:For explanation
40,52,"the Day when the excuses offered by the wrong-doers shall not avail them. They shall be victims of the curse and a woeful abode."
40,53,"We surely guided Moses {1} and made the Children of Israel the heirs of the Book",footnotes:1:That is
40,54,"which was a guidance and good counsel to people endowed with understanding and wisdom. {1}",footnotes:1:That is just as those who disbelieved in Moses (peace be upon him) were deprived of this blessing and the Israelites who believed in him were made heirs to the Book
40,55,"Be steadfast, {1} then, (O Prophet), Allah's promise is true. {2} Seek forgiveness for your shortcomings, {3} and celebrate the praise of your Lord, evening and morning. {4}",footnotes:1:“Have patience”: Bear up with a cool mind against these hardships through which you are passing.|181012:The allusion is to the promise made above in the sentence: We do help Our Messengers and the believers in the life of this world.|181013:A study of the context shows that here “sin” implies the state of impatience that was being caused to the Prophet (peace be upon him) on account of the severe antagonism
40,56,"Verily those who dispute regarding the Signs of Allah without any evidence that might have come to them, nothing but vain pride fills their hearts. Yet they shall never be able to satisfy the pride {1} with which they are puffed up. {2} So seek refuge with Allah. {3} Verily He is All-Hearing, All-Seeing.",footnotes:1:In other words it means: He whom Allah has made great
40,57,"Surely {1} the creation of the heavens and the earth is a greater act than the creation of human beings. But most people do not know. {2}",footnotes:1:After reviewing the conspiracies and plots of the chiefs of the Quraish in (verses 21-56)
40,58,"Never can the blind and the seeing be equal; nor those that believe and act righteously and those that do evil. Little do you understand. {1}",footnotes:1:This is an argument for the necessity of the Hereafter. In the preceding sentence it was said that the Hereafter can take place
